3. High Availability

👉 Cloud services stay running most of the time (24/7) even if something fails.
✔ If one server goes down, another takes over automatically.

📈 14. Scalability

👉 Ability to increase or decrease resources (CPU, storage, users) when needed.
✔ Example: Website gets more users → cloud adds more servers.

🔄 15. Elasticity

👉 Automatic scaling based on demand.
✔ Resources increase during peak time and decrease when not needed.

💡 Difference:

Scalability = planned growth
Elasticity = automatic adjustment
🛡️ 16. Reliability

👉 Cloud systems are stable and less likely to fail.
✔ Data is backed up in multiple locations.

📊 17. Predictability

👉 You can estimate performance, cost, and behavior easily.
✔ Helps in planning budgets and resources.

🔐 18. Security

👉 Cloud providers protect data using:

encryption
firewalls
authentication

✔ But user also must follow security practices.

⚖️ 19. Governance

👉 Rules and policies to control how cloud resources are used.
✔ Ensures compliance, security, and proper usage.

🛠️ 20. Manageability

👉 Easy to monitor, control, and manage cloud resources.
✔ Use dashboards to manage servers, apps, storage.

